1
00:00:04,970 --> 00:00:07,520
Let's not get a divorce.

2
00:00:07,520 --> 00:00:08,980
What are you talking about?

3
00:00:08,980 --> 00:00:13,640
I... don't want to see you getting hurt.

4
00:00:17,220 --> 00:00:18,570
What?
<i>[Divorce Papers, Koichi Obara]</i>

5
00:00:20,230 --> 00:00:21,190
Divorce?

6
00:00:21,190 --> 00:00:23,420
<i>Hello?</i>

7
00:00:23,420 --> 00:00:25,870
S-Sorry, yes...

8
00:00:28,740 --> 00:00:30,400
Huh?

9
00:00:32,700 --> 00:00:34,160
<i>[Divorce paper]</i>

10
00:00:41,090 --> 00:00:42,800
Divorce?

11
00:00:47,060 --> 00:00:57,100
<i>Timing and Subtitles brought to you by
ğŸ‚ğŸŒ»Stay Together TeamğŸ‚ğŸŒ» @ viki.com</i>

12
00:00:59,420 --> 00:01:01,760
Koichi...

13
00:01:01,760 --> 00:01:03,590
Thank you.

14
00:01:04,280 --> 00:01:05,380
It's fine.

15
00:01:05,380 --> 00:01:07,010
Let's start over.

16
00:01:07,010 --> 00:01:10,180
- From the beginning.
- Yes.

17
00:01:10,180 --> 00:01:14,450
We'll be real newlyweds from now on.

18
00:01:14,450 --> 00:01:15,620
Yes.

19
00:01:21,540 --> 00:01:23,700
Are you okay? I'm sorry.

20
00:01:23,700 --> 00:01:25,300
Sorry.

21
00:01:38,530 --> 00:01:40,070
Cheers! That was a "cheers"!

22
00:01:40,070 --> 00:01:42,580
- Ch-Cheers...
- Cheers.

23
00:01:45,270 --> 00:01:48,450
So you can take a bath first, Koichi.

24
00:01:48,450 --> 00:01:50,160
N-No, you can go first.

25
00:01:50,160 --> 00:01:52,560
- No, you go first!
- No, you!

26
00:01:55,650 --> 00:01:56,970
Yes, Koichi speaking.

27
00:01:56,970 --> 00:01:59,610
<i>Mom came home.</i>

28
00:02:08,030 --> 00:02:10,090
Sorry about the wait!

29
00:02:10,090 --> 00:02:11,800
Koichi,

30
00:02:11,800 --> 00:02:14,320
Saki... Thanks for before!

31
00:02:14,320 --> 00:02:17,720
Mom, what's with that-that shirt?

32
00:02:17,720 --> 00:02:20,650
This? I got it from one of my seniors at work.

33
00:02:20,650 --> 00:02:24,200
- It's a group called The Ladies, and-
- That's enough about that!

34
00:02:24,200 --> 00:02:27,840
Go and cook something. I haven't eaten anything decent lately.

35
00:02:27,840 --> 00:02:30,550
Please, don't misunderstand this.

36
00:02:30,550 --> 00:02:33,780
I have not come back home.

37
00:02:33,780 --> 00:02:35,350
But...

38
00:02:36,240 --> 00:02:39,470
I just wanted to show you this.

39
00:02:39,470 --> 00:02:41,840
It's my payslip.

40
00:02:41,840 --> 00:02:44,300
It's the money I earned

41
00:02:44,300 --> 00:02:47,530
in the month I've worked.

42
00:02:49,440 --> 00:02:53,160
You didn't think I could do it, did you?

43
00:02:53,160 --> 00:02:56,370
I was worried too, but...

44
00:02:57,030 --> 00:02:59,100
I did it.

45
00:03:00,480 --> 00:03:03,970
You wouldn't have taken the divorce seriously

46
00:03:03,970 --> 00:03:07,280
unless I left the house like this.

47
00:03:07,970 --> 00:03:11,120
They're going to officially hire me starting next month.

48
00:03:11,120 --> 00:03:15,330
Before then, I want to get the family register sorted out.

49
00:03:18,800 --> 00:03:22,870
Please, sign the divorce papers.

50
00:03:29,580 --> 00:03:31,700
Give me time.

51
00:03:31,700 --> 00:03:35,340
You already had plenty of time!

52
00:03:36,260 --> 00:03:39,060
It's already late...

53
00:03:39,060 --> 00:03:40,770
Why don't we continue this tomorrow?

54
00:03:40,770 --> 00:03:42,900
Mom, please use this room.

55
00:03:42,900 --> 00:03:46,260
- I'll go get a futon.
- I'm not spending the night.

56
00:03:46,260 --> 00:03:49,710
I no longer live in this house.

57
00:03:49,710 --> 00:03:53,090
- Stay over.
- I can't do that.

58
00:03:54,860 --> 00:03:56,700
Stay over!

59
00:04:01,940 --> 00:04:03,590
Wait.

60
00:04:03,590 --> 00:04:07,540
Would you let us spend the night here too?

61
00:04:07,540 --> 00:04:11,540
Let's all spend the night here.

62
00:04:11,540 --> 00:04:15,370
There's a favor I wanted to ask you too.

63
00:04:17,540 --> 00:04:19,160
Cooking?

64
00:04:19,160 --> 00:04:21,890
Yes. Please teach me how to cook tomorrow.

65
00:04:21,890 --> 00:04:23,220
I'd like to

66
00:04:23,220 --> 00:04:27,480
learn how to make Koichi's favorite things.

67
00:04:42,970 --> 00:04:46,890
0400 hours! Rise!

68
00:04:46,890 --> 00:04:49,280
- Do you wake up at 4 a.m. at your parents' house too?
- Yes.

69
00:04:49,280 --> 00:04:51,580
I spend two hours working out.

70
00:04:51,580 --> 00:04:53,590
- Two hours?
- Mom!

71
00:04:59,320 --> 00:05:00,190
Good morning!

72
00:05:00,190 --> 00:05:02,810
Good morning.

73
00:05:02,810 --> 00:05:04,710
Where's Mom?

74
00:05:09,630 --> 00:05:11,210
Never mind.

75
00:05:12,760 --> 00:05:14,760
S-Saki.

76
00:05:18,150 --> 00:05:19,050
Reflect!

77
00:05:19,050 --> 00:05:21,510
Hast thou not gone against sincerity?

78
00:05:21,510 --> 00:05:22,490
Reflect!

79
00:05:22,490 --> 00:05:24,520
Hast thou not felt ashamed of thy words and deeds?

80
00:05:24,520 --> 00:05:25,480
Reflect!

81
00:05:25,480 --> 00:05:27,710
Hast thou not lacked vigor?

82
00:05:27,710 --> 00:05:30,450
Finished! Let's put forth our best effort again today!

83
00:05:30,450 --> 00:05:31,960
- Yes, sir!
- Yes, sir!

84
00:05:33,070 --> 00:05:34,670
I'm going out for a run!

85
00:05:34,670 --> 00:05:36,750
Me too!

86
00:05:39,070 --> 00:05:41,100
Have a good run!

87
00:05:45,560 --> 00:05:47,830
- I'll help.
- It's fine.

88
00:05:47,830 --> 00:05:50,230
Could you help me carry it when it's done?

89
00:05:50,230 --> 00:05:51,790
Sure.

90
00:05:56,910 --> 00:05:59,660
It looks good, right Dad?

91
00:06:04,360 --> 00:06:07,150
Well, shall we get started?

92
00:06:07,150 --> 00:06:10,910
Um... What about Dad's food?

93
00:06:10,910 --> 00:06:14,830
The rice is in the rice cooker, and the sides are on the counter.

94
00:06:14,830 --> 00:06:16,700
Then get it.

95
00:06:18,530 --> 00:06:19,710
Get it!

96
00:06:19,810 --> 00:06:23,040
I'm not your wife anymore.

97
00:06:27,010 --> 00:06:28,270
I'll get it.

98
00:06:28,270 --> 00:06:30,500
- No, I'll get it.
- It's fine!

99
00:06:30,500 --> 00:06:32,660
I'm going to eat out.

100
00:06:35,190 --> 00:06:37,930
Well, let's eat!

101
00:06:37,930 --> 00:06:39,830
Eat up!

102
00:06:39,830 --> 00:06:41,760
Thanks for the food.

103
00:06:50,620 --> 00:06:53,450
<i>[How to Get a Divorce for the Whole Family!]</i>

104
00:06:59,670 --> 00:07:02,920
We're back!

105
00:07:11,780 --> 00:07:15,150
- That was heavy, right?
- It was!

106
00:07:15,150 --> 00:07:19,780
Oh, that cabbage looks good!

107
00:07:19,780 --> 00:07:23,060
Well, let's get started.

108
00:07:26,160 --> 00:07:27,650
Oh!

109
00:07:28,830 --> 00:07:30,640
Just a second.

110
00:07:30,640 --> 00:07:32,900
<i>[Why don't you and Koichi come over for lunch?]</i>

111
00:07:32,900 --> 00:07:34,620
What's wrong?

112
00:07:34,620 --> 00:07:38,390
My dad just asked if you and I would come over now.

113
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:41,620
After what happened, I am worried about him.

114
00:07:41,620 --> 00:07:44,790
<i>We are getting a divorce!</i>

115
00:07:44,790 --> 00:07:47,940
<i>This can't be happening!</i>

116
00:07:48,900 --> 00:07:51,680
We can't go today.

117
00:07:54,050 --> 00:07:55,790
I'll go.

118
00:07:56,530 --> 00:07:58,270
I'm worried about your dad too.

119
00:07:58,270 --> 00:08:02,020
I'll see it as a mission and report back to you.

120
00:08:02,020 --> 00:08:04,450
- Thank you.
- It's fine.

121
00:08:04,450 --> 00:08:07,310
I'll work hard with cooking too.

122
00:08:09,480 --> 00:08:11,630
<i>[Episode Five]</i>

123
00:08:11,630 --> 00:08:13,370
Yes?

124
00:08:14,970 --> 00:08:17,980
I-I've made a mistake. Excuse me!

125
00:08:26,100 --> 00:08:29,190
What's going on?
<i>[Mizuguchi]</i>

126
00:08:32,550 --> 00:08:36,090
Oh, Koichi! Good of you to come!

127
00:08:39,800 --> 00:08:42,120
Um... who is she?

128
00:08:42,120 --> 00:08:43,280
Rinacchi.

129
00:08:43,280 --> 00:08:45,800
Rina-Rinacchi?

130
00:08:45,800 --> 00:08:48,350
Rinacchi...
<i>[Rinacchi]</i>

131
00:08:48,350 --> 00:08:50,210
Rina...

132
00:08:51,270 --> 00:08:53,740
Miss Rinacchi!

133
00:08:53,740 --> 00:08:57,140
I'm very sorry, but could you go home?

134
00:08:57,140 --> 00:09:02,680
- Why?
- Entering a man's house when his wife is gone is immoral!

135
00:09:02,680 --> 00:09:04,110
It's inexcusable!

136
00:09:04,110 --> 00:09:06,230
What's with this guy? Is he a samurai?

137
00:09:06,230 --> 00:09:07,670
He's scary!

138
00:09:07,670 --> 00:09:11,340
Koichi, it's not like that. You have the wrong idea!

139
00:09:11,340 --> 00:09:14,280
Rinacchi is just a friend. Nothing more!

140
00:09:14,280 --> 00:09:15,700
A friend?

141
00:09:15,700 --> 00:09:18,510
But if anyone were to see this...

142
00:09:18,510 --> 00:09:20,040
You're so stuffy!

143
00:09:20,040 --> 00:09:22,590
You really are a serious guy, huh?

144
00:09:22,590 --> 00:09:26,020
What's nonsense is that people would think that.

145
00:09:26,020 --> 00:09:29,700
They're just jealous they can't make friends of the opposite sex!

146
00:09:29,700 --> 00:09:30,990
- Right?
- Right?

147
00:09:30,990 --> 00:09:33,670
I came here because I was really worried.

148
00:09:33,670 --> 00:09:35,580
I thought you might have been seriously depressed.

149
00:09:35,580 --> 00:09:39,660
I am depressed, as you can see!

150
00:09:39,660 --> 00:09:41,260
<i>[Rinacchi]</i>

151
00:09:43,680 --> 00:09:46,970
There isn't anything I can report to her.

152
00:09:49,230 --> 00:09:51,180
Is someone else coming?

153
00:09:51,180 --> 00:09:53,890
Koichi, could you get that for me?

154
00:09:53,890 --> 00:09:56,550
- Sorry about the wait-
- Sorry for coming over so suddenly-

155
00:10:00,410 --> 00:10:03,710
It's amazing, Takepon!

156
00:10:03,710 --> 00:10:05,760
Isn't it great, Rinacchi?

157
00:10:05,760 --> 00:10:07,520
Oh my god!

158
00:10:07,520 --> 00:10:10,020
Come on you two, eat up!

159
00:10:10,020 --> 00:10:12,650
There won't to be any meat left.

160
00:10:12,650 --> 00:10:14,080
Here you go.

161
00:10:14,080 --> 00:10:16,250
So what's wrong, Takaya?

162
00:10:16,250 --> 00:10:17,890
Didn't you need something?

163
00:10:17,890 --> 00:10:20,020
Crap! The meat got away from me.

164
00:10:20,020 --> 00:10:23,130
I can't really say now.

165
00:10:23,130 --> 00:10:25,040
It's fine, it's fine!

166
00:10:25,040 --> 00:10:29,260
I've got nothing to hide anymore, so say it!

167
00:10:30,300 --> 00:10:34,470
Actually... today, I've come as a lawyer.

168
00:10:34,470 --> 00:10:38,510
Midori asked me to give this to you.

169
00:10:43,150 --> 00:10:45,610
<i>[Divorce Papers]</i>

170
00:10:45,610 --> 00:10:48,500
No way! I've never seen one before in real life!
<i>[Midori Mizuguchi]</i>

171
00:10:48,500 --> 00:10:53,890
- Oh my god, Takepon! What a blow!
- Excuse me! Quiet!

172
00:10:53,890 --> 00:10:55,640
There, there...

173
00:11:05,190 --> 00:11:09,070
<i>Koichi's trying to understand her feelings much more than you are.</i>

174
00:11:09,070 --> 00:11:10,670
<i>Enough!</i>

175
00:11:11,980 --> 00:11:14,990
I'm very sorry about the other day.

176
00:11:14,990 --> 00:11:16,950
I went too far.

177
00:11:16,950 --> 00:11:19,210
You've got guts coming here.

178
00:11:24,690 --> 00:11:27,280
May I take the paper?

179
00:11:28,000 --> 00:11:29,140
Do you want to read it?

180
00:11:29,140 --> 00:11:30,980
For the food scraps.

181
00:11:30,980 --> 00:11:32,930
Old papers are over there!

182
00:11:32,930 --> 00:11:34,820
Sorry.

183
00:11:36,730 --> 00:11:41,720
She's not interested in the house or any settlement money, so just sign and stamp here

184
00:11:41,720 --> 00:11:44,580
and send it back to my office before the week's end.

185
00:11:44,580 --> 00:11:46,280
Where is Midori right now?

186
00:11:46,280 --> 00:11:50,610
She's living in an apartment she rented to start a new company.

187
00:11:50,610 --> 00:11:55,330
She wants to clear up the family registry before registering her company.

188
00:12:08,910 --> 00:12:11,590
He's so scary!

189
00:12:11,590 --> 00:12:13,390
Mom!

190
00:12:14,350 --> 00:12:15,890
Sorry about that.

191
00:12:15,890 --> 00:12:17,290
Thank you.

192
00:12:17,290 --> 00:12:21,970
If you make a packet with this and put the food scraps inside, it won't smell.

193
00:12:24,710 --> 00:12:25,640
Oh!

194
00:12:25,640 --> 00:12:28,460
Again?
<i>[Ren Minazuki]</i>

195
00:12:29,410 --> 00:12:32,070
- Yes?
- Get over here now.

196
00:12:32,070 --> 00:12:34,510
Today's my day off, so...

197
00:12:34,510 --> 00:12:37,950
I don't care, come. If you don't...

198
00:12:40,500 --> 00:12:42,600
Saki, what's wrong?

199
00:12:42,600 --> 00:12:45,400
That was the author I'm managing.

200
00:12:45,400 --> 00:12:47,870
He told me to come over right now.

201
00:12:47,870 --> 00:12:50,700
What's his deal? It's my day off.

202
00:12:51,550 --> 00:12:53,390
Why don't you go?

203
00:12:54,090 --> 00:12:58,900
- But you're helping me-
- I can teach you this any time.

204
00:13:00,750 --> 00:13:05,150
I know you're worried about Koichi's father and me, but it'll be fine.

205
00:13:05,150 --> 00:13:06,590
I'm sorry!

206
00:13:06,590 --> 00:13:08,540
I'll go.

207
00:13:10,450 --> 00:13:12,800
Here are some macarons as a gift.

208
00:13:12,800 --> 00:13:14,320
Thank you.

209
00:13:14,320 --> 00:13:18,340
Don't tell Saki about the divorce papers yet.

210
00:13:18,340 --> 00:13:22,260
- But...
- It's a promise between father and son!

211
00:13:22,870 --> 00:13:24,840
Wait!

212
00:13:25,860 --> 00:13:27,700
Obara.

213
00:13:31,920 --> 00:13:33,690
Here.

214
00:13:33,690 --> 00:13:35,460
<i>[Divorce Papers]</i>

215
00:13:37,760 --> 00:13:40,280
Why do you have this?

216
00:13:40,280 --> 00:13:43,610
I took it by mistake at Midori's birthday party.

217
00:13:43,610 --> 00:13:45,390
I'm sorry.

218
00:13:46,450 --> 00:13:48,310
Does Saki know?

219
00:13:48,310 --> 00:13:51,260
That you've written up something like that?

220
00:13:51,260 --> 00:13:55,370
Yes. I gave this to her.

221
00:13:57,200 --> 00:13:59,940
In that case...

222
00:13:59,940 --> 00:14:04,730
Are you two in talks for a divorce?

223
00:14:04,730 --> 00:14:08,040
- Is something wrong?
- No, I'm just concerned.

224
00:14:08,940 --> 00:14:11,520
It's all fine, then.

225
00:14:11,520 --> 00:14:14,410
We decided to start over.

226
00:14:18,300 --> 00:14:20,950
<i>I'm sorry!
[M.R Office]</i>

227
00:14:20,950 --> 00:14:22,390
Pardon me!

228
00:14:22,390 --> 00:14:24,130
Slowpoke!

229
00:14:25,380 --> 00:14:29,420
If you were one minute later, I would've gone to another publisher.

230
00:14:29,420 --> 00:14:32,220
I'm sorry. I came from Mito today.

231
00:14:32,220 --> 00:14:34,940
Read that.

232
00:14:34,940 --> 00:14:36,790
What is it?

233
00:14:36,790 --> 00:14:38,350
My new novel.

234
00:14:38,350 --> 00:14:40,190
I'll read it over!

235
00:14:49,500 --> 00:14:51,810
That's all I've written so far.

236
00:14:51,810 --> 00:14:52,810
What do you think?

237
00:14:52,810 --> 00:14:55,620
It's very interesting!

238
00:14:55,620 --> 00:14:58,100
That's a dull impression.

239
00:14:59,190 --> 00:15:03,510
Your subtle and beautiful writing pierced my heart.

240
00:15:03,510 --> 00:15:06,850
All the characters are appealing too.

241
00:15:06,850 --> 00:15:11,160
I feel like this will be a pure romance novel no one but you could write.

242
00:15:12,340 --> 00:15:14,880
How many tens of thousands do you think it'll sell?

243
00:15:16,120 --> 00:15:20,030
Do you care about that kind of stuff?

244
00:15:20,030 --> 00:15:23,360
If they don't sell, I'm the one getting fired.

245
00:15:25,440 --> 00:15:28,330
I thought an author at your level

246
00:15:28,330 --> 00:15:32,660
could write whatever they wanted to.

247
00:15:37,110 --> 00:15:42,200
I'm sorry. I don't mean that you're not writing what you want to.

248
00:15:43,730 --> 00:15:47,440
You're not getting this novel anymore.

249
00:15:48,710 --> 00:15:50,030
I'm sorry for misspeaking!

250
00:15:50,030 --> 00:15:51,720
Please reconsider!

251
00:15:51,720 --> 00:15:55,740
If you pull the manuscript from the company now...

252
00:15:56,980 --> 00:16:00,970
That's not what I mean. I want to write something new.

253
00:16:00,970 --> 00:16:01,390
What?

254
00:16:02,710 --> 00:16:07,880
If you could be in charge of a book of mine that broke new grounds,

255
00:16:07,880 --> 00:16:09,950
wouldn't you want that?

256
00:16:09,950 --> 00:16:13,690
I think you'll even get attention in the Literature Department.

257
00:16:14,810 --> 00:16:18,100
But in exchange, I have one condition.

258
00:16:18,100 --> 00:16:19,870
What is it?

259
00:16:25,870 --> 00:16:28,080
Be my go-to advisor.

260
00:16:28,080 --> 00:16:31,200
It might give me hints for the novel.

261
00:16:35,020 --> 00:16:37,110
<i>How is married life?</i>

262
00:16:37,110 --> 00:16:39,140
Do you have any complaints?

263
00:16:39,690 --> 00:16:43,260
Before, I always lived exactly as I wanted,

264
00:16:43,260 --> 00:16:46,270
but now I have to consider his schedule too,

265
00:16:46,270 --> 00:16:51,800
and our food and interior design tastes are totally different.

266
00:16:52,350 --> 00:16:55,130
Then why did you get married?

267
00:16:55,130 --> 00:16:58,200
What's the point of being married?

268
00:16:58,200 --> 00:16:59,880
Because...

269
00:16:59,880 --> 00:17:03,150
I'm betting on this marriage.

270
00:17:04,280 --> 00:17:06,310
What about you?

271
00:17:06,310 --> 00:17:08,670
Do you have a family?

272
00:17:14,930 --> 00:17:17,070
Look at the time.

273
00:17:18,670 --> 00:17:22,040
I'm sorry. I'll be leaving for today.

274
00:17:26,940 --> 00:17:28,440
I'm home!

275
00:17:28,440 --> 00:17:29,850
Welcome home.

276
00:17:29,850 --> 00:17:31,440
I'm sorry for being so late!

277
00:17:31,440 --> 00:17:33,820
I just got home too.

278
00:17:33,820 --> 00:17:39,940
I convinced Mom to stay home until Dad signs the divorce papers.

279
00:17:39,940 --> 00:17:43,390
But of course, she won't take care of him.

280
00:17:43,390 --> 00:17:47,640
I hope they can talk about things before they divorce.

281
00:17:49,430 --> 00:17:51,790
Mom gave me lots of her food.

282
00:17:51,790 --> 00:17:53,540
Let's have some together.

283
00:17:54,610 --> 00:17:56,780
I'm okay, I'm okay.

284
00:17:59,150 --> 00:18:01,710
It looks so good,

285
00:18:01,710 --> 00:18:04,320
but it's such a shame.

286
00:18:04,320 --> 00:18:07,210
I really thought I would learn about cooking from your mom.

287
00:18:07,210 --> 00:18:10,410
You can learn from her whenever.

288
00:18:15,060 --> 00:18:17,220
That was so good!

289
00:18:17,220 --> 00:18:18,830
I'm satisfied.

290
00:18:18,830 --> 00:18:20,690
Surely, you can say that another way?

291
00:18:20,690 --> 00:18:24,460
I'm satisfied, so I said I'm satisfied!

292
00:18:25,300 --> 00:18:28,380
That reminds me, how was Dad?

293
00:18:28,380 --> 00:18:29,860
You said you'd report back to me, right?

294
00:18:29,860 --> 00:18:31,530
Show me your notes.

295
00:18:33,560 --> 00:18:34,670
<i>[Rinacchi]</i>

296
00:18:35,750 --> 00:18:36,920
- Let me see!
- No.

297
00:18:36,920 --> 00:18:38,190
Why not?

298
00:18:38,190 --> 00:18:39,850
It's a confidential matter.

299
00:18:39,850 --> 00:18:42,220
- Huh? Let me see!
- More importantly,

300
00:18:42,220 --> 00:18:44,570
how did work go?

301
00:18:44,570 --> 00:18:46,350
With that Mikazuki guy?

302
00:18:46,350 --> 00:18:48,550
- Minazuki!
- Minazuki, huh?

303
00:18:48,550 --> 00:18:54,260
He said he was going to challenge himself to write something totally different.

304
00:18:54,260 --> 00:18:56,900
I know it'll be great.

305
00:18:57,940 --> 00:19:01,970
I'll work hard to make it great.

306
00:19:01,970 --> 00:19:04,060
I see.

307
00:19:04,060 --> 00:19:06,280
That's great.

308
00:19:06,280 --> 00:19:07,460
Oh, that's right.

309
00:19:07,460 --> 00:19:12,420
I got some macarons from your dad. Let's...

310
00:19:13,330 --> 00:19:15,590
Saki?

311
00:20:25,400 --> 00:20:26,990
Good night.

312
00:20:30,110 --> 00:20:31,740
<i>What did you want to talk to me about?</i>

313
00:20:31,740 --> 00:20:36,110
<i>Actually, Master Sergeant Obara, there's been talk of transferring you.</i>

314
00:20:36,110 --> 00:20:42,140
Some of the higher-ups are concerned that you live 90 minutes away.

315
00:20:43,220 --> 00:20:47,790
I told them that you've had no issues carrying out your missions so far.

316
00:20:48,360 --> 00:20:53,690
Personally, I'd like an excellent medic like you to stay with us forever.

317
00:20:54,250 --> 00:20:56,360
Thank you very much.

318
00:20:56,850 --> 00:21:00,620
However, if anything were to happen, I couldn't protect you.

319
00:21:00,620 --> 00:21:03,350
Can you really not move closer to the base?

320
00:21:04,360 --> 00:21:07,380
But my wife works too...

321
00:21:07,380 --> 00:21:09,780
- Talk it over with your wife.
- Yes, sir.

322
00:21:12,230 --> 00:21:16,210
<i>[Authorized Personnel Only]</i>

323
00:21:21,550 --> 00:21:25,060
You can get a new manuscript from Ren Minazuki?

324
00:21:25,060 --> 00:21:27,480
- Yes!
- Great work!

325
00:21:27,480 --> 00:21:29,870
Is that such a happy thing?

326
00:21:29,870 --> 00:21:35,290
Ren Minazuki used to be a powerhouse, but he's past his prime now.

327
00:21:35,290 --> 00:21:37,470
The quality of his novels has tanked, hasn't it?

328
00:21:37,470 --> 00:21:41,520
Even so, the masses will gladly buy Ren Minazuki novels.

329
00:21:41,520 --> 00:21:45,260
Even if it's a rehash of his old stuff, it's sure to be a hit!

330
00:21:45,260 --> 00:21:48,650
The company can expect a huge profit!

331
00:21:48,650 --> 00:21:51,950
I don't think Minazuki is past his prime.

332
00:21:51,950 --> 00:21:54,770
I think now he's going to write what he wants to.

333
00:21:54,770 --> 00:21:57,360
He's going to break new grounds.

334
00:21:57,360 --> 00:22:00,330
His next novel will be a step in a new direction!

335
00:22:00,330 --> 00:22:03,150
If Minazuki can really break new grounds with this,

336
00:22:03,150 --> 00:22:06,690
your life as an editor will absolutely change as well.

337
00:22:06,690 --> 00:22:10,300
This next year will be critical. Make it happen!

338
00:22:10,300 --> 00:22:11,690
Yes, ma'am!

339
00:22:16,270 --> 00:22:17,490
I'm home.

340
00:22:17,490 --> 00:22:19,350
Welcome home!

341
00:22:20,690 --> 00:22:22,110
You're cooking?

342
00:22:22,110 --> 00:22:24,640
I finally got time to do it today.

343
00:22:24,640 --> 00:22:26,630
- What are you making?
- Pad Thai

344
00:22:26,630 --> 00:22:27,950
Pad Thai?

345
00:22:27,950 --> 00:22:30,250
It's like Thai Yakisoba.

346
00:22:34,240 --> 00:22:37,010
I don't know if that's accurate.

347
00:22:37,010 --> 00:22:40,980
I went to a Thai place with Natsumi the other day, and it was really good.

348
00:22:40,980 --> 00:22:43,480
I wanted you to try some too.

349
00:22:45,750 --> 00:22:47,850
Starting tomorrow,

350
00:22:47,850 --> 00:22:50,730
I'm going to leave for work 30 minutes earlier.

351
00:22:50,730 --> 00:22:52,030
Why?

352
00:22:52,030 --> 00:22:53,260
Well...

353
00:22:53,260 --> 00:22:55,100
actually...

354
00:22:57,180 --> 00:22:59,080
I'm sorry, what did you say?

355
00:23:00,070 --> 00:23:02,030
It's a long story. I'll tell you after.

356
00:23:02,030 --> 00:23:03,570
I'm sorry.

357
00:23:04,380 --> 00:23:05,550
Sorry!

358
00:23:05,550 --> 00:23:06,930
Yes?

359
00:23:07,860 --> 00:23:10,410
Listen, can you talk right now?

360
00:23:10,410 --> 00:23:12,630
Yes, it's fine!

361
00:23:13,440 --> 00:23:15,060
I'm sorry!

362
00:23:18,390 --> 00:23:20,050
Whoa!

363
00:23:21,410 --> 00:23:24,330
What do I do with this?

364
00:23:24,330 --> 00:23:28,880
That's true. It's a little simple.

365
00:23:28,880 --> 00:23:30,590
I knew it.

366
00:23:30,590 --> 00:23:31,710
Huh?

367
00:23:31,710 --> 00:23:36,180
No, Mr. Minazuki, I don't mean that in such a negative sense.

368
00:23:36,180 --> 00:23:37,320
For example...

369
00:23:37,320 --> 00:23:40,690
Well, for example...

370
00:23:59,070 --> 00:24:02,510
It is Yakisoba. Japanese sauces are universal.

371
00:24:14,620 --> 00:24:16,930
<i>Yes.</i>

372
00:24:16,930 --> 00:24:19,220
<i>I see.</i>

373
00:24:19,220 --> 00:24:22,320
<i>I see. Yes, that's true.</i>

374
00:24:22,320 --> 00:24:27,500
Mr. Minazuki, I think you can go beyond the framework of a romance novel.

375
00:24:27,500 --> 00:24:30,900
- Yes.
- Are you not finished yet?

376
00:24:30,900 --> 00:24:32,140
Yes.

377
00:24:34,190 --> 00:24:36,310
You go ahead to bed. Good night!

378
00:24:36,310 --> 00:24:39,410
Yes. I'm listening.

379
00:24:39,410 --> 00:24:41,260
Yes.

380
00:24:41,260 --> 00:24:44,350
- I see.
- Good night.

381
00:24:49,670 --> 00:24:51,990
0330 hours! Rise!

382
00:25:15,940 --> 00:25:17,290
No way!

383
00:25:17,290 --> 00:25:19,280
I fell asleep?

384
00:25:19,280 --> 00:25:22,130
Hello? Hello?

385
00:25:32,520 --> 00:25:35,400
What do I do? I bet I made him angry!

386
00:25:35,400 --> 00:25:38,280
Of course, you'd get sleepy, talking on the phone all night.

387
00:25:38,280 --> 00:25:40,210
It's strange that he'd keep you up!

388
00:25:40,210 --> 00:25:43,880
In the Literature Department, keeping in contact with the author is crucial!

389
00:25:43,880 --> 00:25:46,150
If I make him upset, we won't get his manuscript!

390
00:25:46,150 --> 00:25:47,120
Where are you going?

391
00:25:47,120 --> 00:25:48,830
Mr. Minazuki's place. I need to go and apologize.

392
00:25:48,830 --> 00:25:52,090
Wait. Eat breakfast first, at least.

393
00:25:52,960 --> 00:25:55,120
I'm sorry, I have to run.

394
00:25:55,120 --> 00:25:56,670
Will you be okay with the time, Koichi?

395
00:25:56,670 --> 00:25:58,890
Will you be later than usual because I was asleep?

396
00:25:58,890 --> 00:25:59,920
I'll be fine.

397
00:25:59,920 --> 00:26:02,600
I always leave with plenty of time.

398
00:26:02,600 --> 00:26:06,340
I-I see. I'm sorry, I'm heading out!

399
00:26:10,570 --> 00:26:12,620
<i>On the Joban Motorway,</i>

400
00:26:12,620 --> 00:26:15,640
<i>there's been a multi-car pileup,</i>

401
00:26:15,640 --> 00:26:17,830
<i>which has caused heavy traffic.</i>

402
00:26:17,830 --> 00:26:19,280
<i>We'll repeat that...</i>

403
00:26:19,280 --> 00:26:20,320
<i>On the Joban Motorway...</i>

404
00:26:20,320 --> 00:26:22,980
I'm very sorry. Yes.

405
00:26:22,980 --> 00:26:25,580
Please send Tani in my place.

406
00:26:25,580 --> 00:26:27,750
I'll head that way as soon as I can.

407
00:26:30,100 --> 00:26:31,790
<i>[M.R Office]</i>

408
00:26:31,790 --> 00:26:33,710
It's Obara!

409
00:26:33,710 --> 00:26:36,110
Please, open the door!

410
00:26:40,380 --> 00:26:41,890
<i>[Falling asleep during a phone call is unbelievable]</i>

411
00:26:43,500 --> 00:26:46,120
<i>[You didn't come 30 minutes after hanging up, so no dice]</i>

412
00:26:48,420 --> 00:26:50,080
Mr. Minazuki!

413
00:26:50,080 --> 00:26:51,990
Please give me one more chance!

414
00:26:51,990 --> 00:26:53,940
Please!

415
00:26:54,950 --> 00:26:57,520
Mr. Minazuki!

416
00:27:05,550 --> 00:27:07,870
Leading Private Tani is back!

417
00:27:11,080 --> 00:27:12,750
- Officer!
- Officer!

418
00:27:14,790 --> 00:27:15,900
Did something happen?

419
00:27:15,900 --> 00:27:18,320
Leading Private Tani got injured.

420
00:27:22,650 --> 00:27:23,980
Tani!

421
00:27:23,980 --> 00:27:26,540
I'm sorry! I'm sorry for worrying you.

422
00:27:26,540 --> 00:27:28,140
How's your arm?

423
00:27:28,140 --> 00:27:30,470
Fractured. It'll take a month to heal completely.

424
00:27:30,470 --> 00:27:33,040
I'm sorry. This is because I was late.

425
00:27:33,040 --> 00:27:34,620
Please stop!

426
00:27:34,620 --> 00:27:36,540
This isn't your fault, Master Sergeant Obara.

427
00:27:36,540 --> 00:27:38,170
But...

428
00:27:43,020 --> 00:27:45,140
<i>[Voice call]</i>

429
00:27:45,140 --> 00:27:46,140
<i>[Ren Minazuki]</i>

430
00:27:59,020 --> 00:28:00,780
I'm very sorry.

431
00:28:00,780 --> 00:28:02,490
I will take all of the shifts

432
00:28:02,490 --> 00:28:05,310
Tani was scheduled for!

433
00:28:06,060 --> 00:28:07,640
Don't worry about it.

434
00:28:07,640 --> 00:28:09,990
Any injuries that happen on a mission

435
00:28:09,990 --> 00:28:12,170
are the responsibility of the commanding officer, me.

436
00:28:12,170 --> 00:28:13,080
No...

437
00:28:13,080 --> 00:28:16,920
I couldn't make it in time for my scheduled mission. I am mostly responsible.

438
00:28:16,920 --> 00:28:18,350
And in the first place,

439
00:28:18,350 --> 00:28:20,940
you warned me before

440
00:28:20,940 --> 00:28:24,540
that a situation like this could happen.

441
00:28:24,540 --> 00:28:27,750
Not only now, but in an emergency,

442
00:28:27,750 --> 00:28:31,610
I can't promptly protect my fellow citizens and colleagues.

443
00:28:33,550 --> 00:28:37,320
This has made me keenly aware

444
00:28:37,320 --> 00:28:39,970
that I lack what it takes to be an ARS member.

445
00:28:41,160 --> 00:28:42,910
I'm

446
00:28:42,910 --> 00:28:45,110
incredibly sorry!

447
00:28:53,340 --> 00:28:55,490
<i>[Koichi Obara]</i>

448
00:28:59,310 --> 00:29:02,000
<i>When is he going to come home?</i>

449
00:29:02,000 --> 00:29:05,570
<i>In times like these, I want him beside me.</i>

450
00:29:09,550 --> 00:29:11,400
<i>[Ren Minazuki]</i>

451
00:29:19,690 --> 00:29:22,700
<i>["That others may live"]</i>

452
00:29:32,310 --> 00:29:34,120
Right. Yes.

453
00:29:34,120 --> 00:29:36,120
A downtown scene, right?

454
00:29:36,120 --> 00:29:39,020
I see.

455
00:29:42,060 --> 00:29:44,880
Yes, I think that would be interesting.

456
00:29:44,880 --> 00:29:48,210
Has he kept you on the phone all night again?

457
00:29:48,210 --> 00:29:50,070
Yes! Of course.

458
00:29:50,070 --> 00:29:52,310
There's something I want to talk to you about.

459
00:29:52,310 --> 00:29:54,110
I'm sorry. Later.

460
00:29:54,110 --> 00:29:56,500
No, I am listening.

461
00:29:56,500 --> 00:29:59,490
When is "later"?

462
00:29:59,490 --> 00:30:01,480
Yes, that's right!

463
00:30:01,480 --> 00:30:03,670
I want to talk now!

464
00:30:04,920 --> 00:30:07,390
Um, I'm really sorry.

465
00:30:07,390 --> 00:30:09,350
Could you please hold on for just a second?

466
00:30:09,350 --> 00:30:12,430
No, it's not like that at all-

467
00:30:12,430 --> 00:30:17,310
What time do you think it is? It's thoughtless to talk on the phone all night!

468
00:30:19,030 --> 00:30:20,970
What did you do?

469
00:30:20,970 --> 00:30:24,830
He finally said he would give me one more chance, and you ruined it!

470
00:30:24,830 --> 00:30:27,720
You shouldn't be bringing your work home with you!

471
00:30:28,920 --> 00:30:30,970
I haven't even...

472
00:30:30,970 --> 00:30:32,840
seen your face squarely.

473
00:30:32,840 --> 00:30:34,510
I can't help that!

474
00:30:34,510 --> 00:30:37,430
I just got transferred to the Literature Department,

475
00:30:37,430 --> 00:30:39,510
and I'm trying really hard at this job I'm not used to!

476
00:30:39,510 --> 00:30:42,130
So then it's okay to neglect your family?

477
00:30:42,130 --> 00:30:44,180
I'm not neglecting anyone!

478
00:30:44,180 --> 00:30:48,620
- I-
- Then listen to what your husband is telling you now!

479
00:30:48,620 --> 00:30:52,360
What? What's gotten into you lately?

480
00:30:53,850 --> 00:30:55,720
Actually...

481
00:30:57,870 --> 00:31:01,210
I was thinking of moving to my parents' house in Mito.

482
00:31:02,120 --> 00:31:04,600
Will you come with me?

483
00:31:05,180 --> 00:31:06,380
What?

484
00:31:09,470 --> 00:31:12,280
Will you come with me?

485
00:31:12,280 --> 00:31:15,190
Where is this coming from all of a sudden?

486
00:31:15,860 --> 00:31:17,210
What about...

487
00:31:17,210 --> 00:31:19,560
my job?

488
00:31:19,560 --> 00:31:20,500
That's...

489
00:31:20,500 --> 00:31:22,640
Are you telling me to quit my job?

490
00:31:22,640 --> 00:31:25,330
For my work,

491
00:31:25,330 --> 00:31:27,320
I think I should live closer to the base, after all.

492
00:31:27,320 --> 00:31:29,180
But that's the same for me!

493
00:31:29,180 --> 00:31:32,670
I just got transferred! I can't be far from Tokyo, where Minazuki is!

494
00:31:32,670 --> 00:31:33,880
Don't you get that?

495
00:31:33,880 --> 00:31:36,650
Are you saying you'd choose work over living with me?

496
00:31:36,650 --> 00:31:38,480
I didn't say that!

497
00:31:38,480 --> 00:31:40,000
I want both things to coexist!

498
00:31:40,000 --> 00:31:42,300
Coexist? How?

499
00:31:42,300 --> 00:31:43,660
<i>[Ren Minazuki]</i>

500
00:31:45,900 --> 00:31:49,720
It's clear that you will always prioritize work.

501
00:31:50,820 --> 00:31:52,110
<i>[Ren Minazuki]</i>

502
00:31:52,110 --> 00:31:54,420
You're one to talk.

503
00:31:54,420 --> 00:31:58,300
You've always prioritized your work too!

504
00:32:24,020 --> 00:32:27,760
How is Ren Minazuki's new novel going? Well?

505
00:32:27,760 --> 00:32:29,730
It's fine.

506
00:32:29,730 --> 00:32:31,850
After all you've said,

507
00:32:31,850 --> 00:32:33,940
if you ended up not getting the manuscript,

508
00:32:33,940 --> 00:32:38,040
I would be too embarrassed to stay in the Literature Department if it were me.

509
00:32:38,040 --> 00:32:40,220
I said, "It's fine."

510
00:32:40,220 --> 00:32:42,350
You have a visitor.

511
00:32:42,350 --> 00:32:43,860
what?

512
00:33:00,600 --> 00:33:03,280
<i>Sorry for visiting in the middle of work.
[Coffee Shop Galant]</i>

513
00:33:03,280 --> 00:33:06,600
- It's fine.
- I wanted to speak with you,

514
00:33:06,600 --> 00:33:08,860
without Master Sergeant Obara.

515
00:33:08,860 --> 00:33:10,160
What is it?

516
00:33:10,160 --> 00:33:12,830
I've been concerned for a while.

517
00:33:12,830 --> 00:33:14,550
Your house...

518
00:33:14,550 --> 00:33:18,130
It's 90 minutes from the base, isn't it?

519
00:33:21,100 --> 00:33:22,790
The rules do state

520
00:33:22,790 --> 00:33:27,140
that you can live at most, two hours away from the base,

521
00:33:27,140 --> 00:33:29,280
but in reality,

522
00:33:29,280 --> 00:33:32,480
everyone lives within 30 minutes of the base.

523
00:33:33,920 --> 00:33:36,270
I can't bear to see it.

524
00:33:37,140 --> 00:33:38,620
Master Sergeant Obara has been

525
00:33:38,620 --> 00:33:42,740
blaming himself for Leading Private Tani's injury!

526
00:33:43,980 --> 00:33:46,120
What are you talking about?

527
00:33:46,120 --> 00:33:49,030
Tani got injured?

528
00:33:51,660 --> 00:33:54,480
He hasn't told you?

529
00:33:57,340 --> 00:34:01,920
Yesterday morning, Master Sergeant Obara got caught in traffic

530
00:34:01,920 --> 00:34:04,130
and couldn't make it in time for his mission.

531
00:34:04,130 --> 00:34:08,490
Leading Private Tani went instead, and he got injured.

532
00:34:09,720 --> 00:34:11,350
Did you know

533
00:34:11,350 --> 00:34:15,830
there have been talks of transferring Master Sergeant Obara

534
00:34:15,830 --> 00:34:17,700
